on the assumption of the Riemann hypothesis. The best known unconditional bound is
:formula_5
due to Baker, Harman, and Pintz.

In the other direction, E. Westzynthius proved in 1931 that prime gaps grow more than logarithmically. That is,
:formula_6
His result was improved by R. A. Rankin, who proved that
:formula_7
Paul Erdős conjectured that the left-hand side of the above formula is infinite, and this was proven in 2014 by Kevin Ford, Ben Green, Sergei Konyagin, and Terence Tao, and independently by James Maynard. The two sets of authors eliminated one of the factors of formula_8 later that year, showing that, infinitely often,

